cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with saliency methods for highlighting features in input data relevant for the prediction of a learned model. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing saliency methods and proposes a methodology for evaluating them, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
